\h Nahum
\toc1 Nahum
\toc2 Nahum
\mt1 Nahum
\c 1
\p \v 1 \x + \xo 1:1 \xt See Isa. 13:1 \x*An oracle concerning \x + \xo 1:1 \xt ch. 2:8; 3:7; See Jonah 1:2\x*Nineveh. The book of the vision of Nahum of Elkosh.
\s1 God’s Wrath Against Nineveh
\q1
\v 2 \x + \xo 1:2 \xt See Ex. 20:5 \x*The \nd Lord\nd* is a jealous and avenging God;
\q2 the \nd Lord\nd* is avenging and wrathful;
\q1 \x + \xo 1:2 \xt [Ps. 92:9] \x*the \nd Lord\nd* takes vengeance on his adversaries
\q2 and \x + \xo 1:2 \xt [Ps. 103:9]\x*keeps wrath for his enemies.
\q1
\v 3 \x + \xo 1:3 \xt See Ex. 34:6 \x*The \nd Lord\nd* is slow to anger and \x + \xo 1:3 \xt Job 9:4; Ps. 147:5 \x*great in power,
\q2 and \x + \xo 1:3 \xt See Ex. 34:7 \x*the \nd Lord\nd* will by no means clear the guilty.
\q1 \x + \xo 1:3 \xt [Ps. 97:2]; See Ps. 18:9-13\x*His way is in whirlwind and storm,
\q2 and the clouds are the dust of his feet.
\q1
\v 4 \x + \xo 1:4 \xt Ps. 106:9; [Isa. 50:2] \x*He rebukes the sea and makes it dry;
\q2 he dries up all the rivers;
\q1 \x + \xo 1:4 \xt Isa. 33:9 \x*Bashan and \x + \xo 1:4 \xt See Josh. 19:26\x*Carmel wither;
\q2 the bloom of \x + \xo 1:4 \xt Isa. 33:9 \x*Lebanon withers.
\q1
\v 5 \x + \xo 1:5 \xt [Jer. 4:24; Hab. 3:6] \x*The mountains quake before him;
\q2 \x + \xo 1:5 \xt Amos 9:13 \x*the hills melt;
\q1 the earth heaves before him,
\q2 \x + \xo 1:5 \xt Ps. 98:7\x*the world and all who dwell in it.
\b
\q1
\v 6 \x + \xo 1:6 \xt [Mal. 3:2] \x*Who can stand before his indignation?
\q2 Who can endure the heat of his anger?
\q1 His wrath \x + \xo 1:6 \xt 2 Chr. 34:21; [Ps. 79:6] \x*is poured out like fire,
\q2 and \x + \xo 1:6 \xt Ezek. 38:20\x*the rocks are broken into pieces by him.
\q1
\v 7 \x + \xo 1:7 \xt Jer. 33:11; See Ps. 100:5 \x*The \nd Lord\nd* is good,
\q2 \x + \xo 1:7 \xt Ps. 46:1; Isa. 25:4 \x*a stronghold in the day of trouble;
\q1 \x + \xo 1:7 \xt Ps. 1:6; John 10:14, 27; 1 Cor. 8:3; 2 Tim. 2:19\x*he knows those who take refuge in him.
\q2
\v 8 But \x + \xo 1:8 \xt [Isa. 30:28] \x*with an overflowing flood
\q1 he will make a complete end of the adversaries,\f + \fr 1:8 \ft Hebrew \fq of her place\f*
\q2 and \x + \xo 1:8 \xt Isa. 8:22\x*will pursue his enemies into darkness.
\q1
\v 9 What \x + \xo 1:9 \xt [Isa. 10:7] \x*do you plot against the \nd Lord\nd*?
\q2 \x + \xo 1:9 \xt [Jer. 4:27]\x*He will make a complete end;
\q2 trouble will not rise up a second time.
\q1
\v 10 For they are \x + \xo 1:10 \xt See Mic. 7:4 \x*like entangled thorns,
\q2 like drunkards as they drink;
\q2 \x + \xo 1:10 \xt See Joel 2:5\x*they are consumed like stubble fully dried.
\q1
\v 11 From you came one
\q2 \x + \xo 1:11 \xt [ver. 9; 2 Kgs. 19:22, 23]\x*who plotted evil against the \nd Lord\nd*,
\q2 a worthless counselor.
\b
\q1
\v 12 Thus says the \nd Lord\nd*,
\q1 “Though they are at full strength and many,
\q2 \x + \xo 1:12 \xt Isa. 10:33, 34; [Isa. 37:36] \x*they will be cut down and pass away.
\q1 \x + \xo 1:12 \xt ver. 9; [Isa. 9:1]\x*Though I have afflicted you,
\q2 I will afflict you no more.
\q1
\v 13 And now \x + \xo 1:13 \xt [Isa. 9:4; 10:27; 14:25]\x*I will break his yoke from off you
\q2 and will burst your bonds apart.”
\b
\q1
\v 14 The \nd Lord\nd* has given commandment about you:
\q2 \x + \xo 1:14 \xt [Ps. 109:13] \x*“No more shall your name be perpetuated;
\q1 from \x + \xo 1:14 \xt [2 Kgs. 19:37] \x*the house of your gods I will cut off
\q2 the carved image and the metal image.
\q1 \x + \xo 1:14 \xt [Isa. 30:33]; See Ezek. 32:21-23 \x*I will make your grave, \x + \xo 1:14 \xt [ch. 3:6]\x*for you are vile.”
\b
\q1
\v 15 \f + \fr 1:15 \ft Ch 2:1 in Hebrew\f* \x + \xo 1:15 \xt See Isa. 52:7 \x*Behold, upon the mountains, \x + \xo 1:15 \xt [Rom. 10:15] \x*the feet of him
\q2 who brings good news,
\q2 who publishes peace!
\q1 \x + \xo 1:15 \xt [Isa. 30:29] \x*Keep your feasts, O Judah;
\q2 \x + \xo 1:15 \xt See Num. 30:2 \x*fulfill your vows,
\q1 \x + \xo 1:15 \xt [ver. 12]; See Joel 3:17\x*for never again shall the worthless pass through you;
\q2 he is utterly cut off.
\c 2
\s1 The Destruction of Nineveh
\q1 \v 1 \x + \xo 2:1 \xt [Jer. 51:20] \x*The scatterer has come up against you.
\q2 \x + \xo 2:1 \xt [Jer. 51:12]\x*Man the ramparts;
\q2 watch the road;
\q1 dress for battle;\f + \fr 2:1 \ft Hebrew \fq gird your loins\f*
\q2 collect all your strength.
\b
\q1
\v 2 For \x + \xo 2:2 \xt [Isa. 37:31] \x*the \nd Lord\nd* is restoring the majesty of Jacob
\q2 as the majesty of Israel,
\q1 for plunderers have plundered them
\q2 and \x + \xo 2:2 \xt See Ps. 80:8-13; Isa. 5:1-7\x*ruined their branches.
\b
\q1
\v 3 The shield of his mighty men is red;
\q2 \x + \xo 2:3 \xt [Ezek. 23:14, 15]\x*his soldiers are clothed in scarlet.
\q1 The chariots come with flashing metal
\q2 on the day he musters them;
\q2 the cypress spears are brandished.
\q1
\v 4 \x + \xo 2:4 \xt [ch. 3:2]\x*The chariots race madly through the streets;
\q2 they rush to and fro through the squares;
\q1 they gleam like torches;
\q2 they dart like lightning.
\q1
\v 5 He remembers \x + \xo 2:5 \xt ch. 3:18 \x*his officers;
\q2 \x + \xo 2:5 \xt Jer. 46:12\x*they stumble as they go,
\q1 they hasten to the wall;
\q2 the siege tower\f + \fr 2:5 \ft Or \fq the mantelet\f* is set up.
\q1
\v 6 \x + \xo 2:6 \xt [Isa. 45:1] \x*The river gates are opened;
\q2 the palace \x + \xo 2:6 \xt [Isa. 14:31]\x*melts away;
\q1
\v 7 its mistress\f + \fr 2:7 \ft The meaning of the Hebrew word rendered \fq its mistress \ft is uncertain\f* is \x + \xo 2:7 \xt [Isa. 22:8] \x*stripped;\f + \fr 2:7 \ft Or \fq exiled\f* she is carried off,
\q2 her slave girls \x + \xo 2:7 \xt Isa. 38:14\x*lamenting,
\q1 moaning like doves
\q2 and beating their breasts.
\q1
\v 8 \x + \xo 2:8 \xt See ch. 1:1 \x*Nineveh is like a pool
\q2 whose waters run away.\f + \fr 2:8 \ft Compare Septuagint; the meaning of the Hebrew is uncertain\f*
\q1 “Halt! Halt!” they cry,
\q2 but \x + \xo 2:8 \xt Jer. 46:5\x*none turns back.
\q1
\v 9 Plunder the silver,
\q2 plunder the gold!
\q1 There is no end of the treasure
\q2 or of the wealth of all precious things.
\b
\q1
\v 10 \x + \xo 2:10 \xt See Zeph. 2:13-15 \x*Desolate! Desolation and ruin!
\q2 \x + \xo 2:10 \xt Ps. 22:14; Isa. 13:7 \x*Hearts melt and \x + \xo 2:10 \xt Dan. 5:6 \x*knees tremble;
\q1 \x + \xo 2:10 \xt Isa. 21:3 \x*anguish is in all loins;
\q2 \x + \xo 2:10 \xt Joel 2:6\x*all faces grow pale!
\q1
\v 11 Where is the lions’ den,
\q2 the feeding place of \x + \xo 2:11 \xt Isa. 5:29; Jer. 2:15 \x*the young lions,
\q1 where the lion and lioness went,
\q2 where his cubs were, with \x + \xo 2:11 \xt See Isa. 17:2\x*none to disturb?
\q1
\v 12 \x + \xo 2:12 \xt [Ezek. 19:3] \x*The lion tore enough for his cubs
\q2 and \x + \xo 2:12 \xt [ver. 9; ch. 3:1]\x*strangled prey for his lionesses;
\q1 he filled his caves with prey
\q2 and his dens with torn flesh.
\b
\p
\v 13 \x + \xo 2:13 \xt ch. 3:5; [Zeph. 2:5]; See Ezek. 13:8 \x*Behold, I am against you, declares the \nd Lord\nd* of hosts, and \x + \xo 2:13 \xt [Ps. 46:9] \x*I will burn your\f + \fr 2:13 \ft Hebrew \fq her\f* chariots in smoke, and the sword shall devour your young lions. I will cut off your prey from the earth, and \x + \xo 2:13 \xt [2 Kgs. 19:9, 23]\x*the voice of your messengers shall no longer be heard.
\c 3
\s1 Woe to Nineveh
\q1
\v 1 Woe to \x + \xo 3:1 \xt Ezek. 24:9; [Hab. 2:12] \x*the bloody city,
\q2 all full of lies and plunder—
\q2 \x + \xo 3:1 \xt [ch. 2:12]\x*no end to the prey!
\q1
\v 2 The crack of the whip, and \x + \xo 3:2 \xt [ch. 2:4] \x*rumble of the wheel,
\q2 \x + \xo 3:2 \xt [Judg. 5:22] \x*galloping horse and \x + \xo 3:2 \xt [Joel 2:5]\x*bounding chariot!
\q1
\v 3 Horsemen charging,
\q2 flashing sword and \x + \xo 3:3 \xt Hab. 3:11 \x*glittering spear,
\q1 \x + \xo 3:3 \xt [2 Kgs. 19:35]\x*hosts of slain,
\q2 heaps of corpses,
\q1 dead bodies without end—
\q2 they stumble over the bodies!
\q1
\v 4 And all for the countless whorings of the \x + \xo 3:4 \xt [Rev. 17:2; 18:3] \x*prostitute,
\q2 \x + \xo 3:4 \xt [Isa. 47:9, 12]\x*graceful and of deadly charms,
\q1 who betrays nations with her whorings,
\q2 and peoples with her charms.
\b
\q1
\v 5 \x + \xo 3:5 \xt [See ch. 2:13 above] \x*Behold, I am against you,
\q2 declares the \nd Lord\nd* of hosts,
\q2 and \x + \xo 3:5 \xt Jer. 13:22, 26; [Isa. 3:17; 47:3] \x*will lift up your skirts over your face;
\q1 and I will make nations look at \x + \xo 3:5 \xt Hab. 2:16\x*your nakedness
\q2 and kingdoms at your shame.
\q1
\v 6 I will throw filth at you
\q2 and \x + \xo 3:6 \xt Mal. 2:9; [ch. 1:14] \x*treat you with contempt
\q2 and make you \x + \xo 3:6 \xt Heb. 10:33; [1 Cor. 4:9]\x*a spectacle.
\q1
\v 7 And all who look at you \x + \xo 3:7 \xt Jer. 51:9; Rev. 18:10 \x*will shrink from you and say,
\q1 “Wasted is \x + \xo 3:7 \xt [Zeph. 2:13]; See ch. 1:1 \x*Nineveh; \x + \xo 3:7 \xt Isa. 51:19; Jer. 15:5 \x*who will grieve for her?”
\q2 \x + \xo 3:7 \xt Lam. 1:2, 9, 16, 17, 21\x*Where shall I seek comforters for you?
\b
\q1
\v 8 \x + \xo 3:8 \xt [Amos 6:2] \x*Are you better than \x + \xo 3:8 \xt Jer. 46:25 \x*Thebes\f + \fr 3:8 \ft Hebrew \+tl No-amon\+tl*\f*
\q2 that sat \x + \xo 3:8 \xt [Ezek. 29:3]\x*by the Nile,
\q1 with water around her,
\q2 her rampart a sea,
\q2 and water her wall?
\q1
\v 9 \x + \xo 3:9 \xt See Dan. 11:43 \x*Cush was her strength;
\q2 Egypt too, and that without limit;
\q2 \x + \xo 3:9 \xt Gen. 10:6 \x*Put and the \x + \xo 3:9 \xt See 2 Chr. 12:3\x*Libyans were her\f + \fr 3:9 \ft Hebrew \fq your\f* helpers.
\b
\q1
\v 10 \x + \xo 3:10 \xt Isa. 20:4 \x*Yet she became an exile;
\q2 she went into captivity;
\q1 \x + \xo 3:10 \xt Isa. 13:16 \x*her infants were dashed in pieces
\q2 at the head of every street;
\q1 for her honored men \x + \xo 3:10 \xt Joel 3:3; Obad. 11 \x*lots were cast,
\q2 \x + \xo 3:10 \xt [Ps. 149:8]\x*and all her great men were bound in chains.
\q1
\v 11 \x + \xo 3:11 \xt Jer. 25:17, 27; [Ps. 75:8; Isa. 51:17; Obad. 16] \x*You also will be drunken;
\q2 you will go into hiding;
\q1 \x + \xo 3:11 \xt [Jer. 4:5, 6]\x*you will seek a refuge from the enemy.
\q1
\v 12 All your fortresses are \x + \xo 3:12 \xt [Rev. 6:13]\x*like fig trees
\q2 with first-ripe figs—
\q1 if shaken they fall
\q2 into the mouth of the eater.
\q1
\v 13 Behold, your troops
\q2 \x + \xo 3:13 \xt Isa. 19:16; Jer. 51:30\x*are women in your midst.
\q1 The gates of your land
\q2 are wide open to your enemies;
\q2 fire has devoured your bars.
\b
\q1
\v 14 \x + \xo 3:14 \xt [Isa. 22:11] \x*Draw water for the siege;
\q2 \x + \xo 3:14 \xt [See ver. 11 above]\x*strengthen your forts;
\q1 go into the clay;
\q2 tread the mortar;
\q2 take hold of the brick mold!
\q1
\v 15 There will the fire devour you;
\q2 the sword will cut you off.
\q2 It will \x + \xo 3:15 \xt [Joel 2:3] \x*devour you \x + \xo 3:15 \xt [Joel 1:4, 6]\x*like the locust.
\q1 Multiply yourselves \x + \xo 3:15 \xt [Joel 1:4, 6]\x*like the locust;
\q2 multiply \x + \xo 3:15 \xt [Joel 1:4, 6]\x*like the grasshopper!
\q1
\v 16 You increased \x + \xo 3:16 \xt [Ezek. 27:23, 24] \x*your merchants
\q2 more than the stars of the heavens.
\q2 \x + \xo 3:16 \xt [See ver. 15 above]\x*The locust spreads its wings and flies away.
\b
\q1
\v 17 Your \x + \xo 3:17 \xt [Isa. 10:8] \x*princes are \x + \xo 3:17 \xt [See ver. 15 above] \x*like grasshoppers,
\q2 \x + \xo 3:17 \xt Jer. 51:27\x*your scribes\f + \fr 3:17 \ft Or \fq marshals\f* like clouds of locusts
\q1 settling on the fences
\q2 in a day of cold—
\q1 when the sun rises, they fly away;
\q2 no one knows where they are.
\b
\q1
\v 18 Your shepherds \x + \xo 3:18 \xt [Ps. 76:5] \x*are asleep,
\q2 O king of Assyria;
\q2 \x + \xo 3:18 \xt ch. 2:5 \x*your nobles slumber.
\q1 Your people \x + \xo 3:18 \xt [1 Kgs. 22:17]\x*are scattered on the mountains
\q2 with none to gather them.
\q1
\v 19 There is no easing your hurt;
\q2 \x + \xo 3:19 \xt Jer. 10:19; Mic. 1:9 \x*your wound is grievous.
\q1 All who hear the news about you
\q2 \x + \xo 3:19 \xt Lam. 2:15; [Zeph. 2:15] \x*clap their hands over you.
\q1 For \x + \xo 3:19 \xt [Isa. 37:18]\x*upon whom has not come
\q2 your unceasing evil?
